Organized jointly with the [ 9 ] International Symposium on Soft Computing ( SOCO'99 ) in collaboration with Ansaldo Ricerche and DISI-University of Genova , Italy
Call for Papers
Prospective authors are requested to send an extended abstract or a draft paper ( maximum 7 pages ) for review by the International Scientific Committee . All submissions must be written in English , starting with a succinct statement of the problem , the results achieved , their significance and a comparison with previous work , as well as a list of references . The submissions should also include :
[ werbul 1 a . gif ] Title of conference ( IIA'99 or SOCO'99 ) [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Type of paper ( regular , demonstration , tutorial or invited ) [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Title of proposed paper [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Authors names , affiliations , addresses [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Name of author to contact for correspondence [ werbul 1 a . gif ] E- mail address and fax # of contact author [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Topics which best describe the paper ( max . 5 keywords ) [ werbul 1 a . gif ] Short c . v . of authors
Contributions are welcome from those working in industry and having experience in the topics of this symposium as well as from academics .
Symposium language is English . [ 10 ] Invited Sessions , tutorial papers , [ 11 ] Demonstrations and contributions to the special session on [ 12 ] Intelligent Systems in Control and Process Optimization are also encouraged

Important Dates
Extended Submission Deadline September 30 , 1998 Notification of Acceptance November 30 , 1998 Delivery of Full Papers January 31 , 1999 Tutorials and Workshops June 1 , 1999 IIA'99 / SOCO'99 Symposia June 2 - 4 , 1999

Demonstration Sessions Instead of submitting a paper , proposals for a 20 minute demonstration of a practical application can also be submitted . A regular 220 V power outlet and a VHS-video recorder will be available in the demonstration room . The demonstration proposal should follow the regular abstract submission guidelines . Only the abstract ( 500 - 1000 words ) of the demonstration will be printed in the conference proceedings .
[ werhsepa . gif ]
Invited Sessions Prospective organizers of invited sessions are requested to send a session proposal ( consisting of 4 - 5 invited paper abstracts , the recommended session-chair and co-chair , as well as a short statement describing the title and the purpose of the session to the [ 14 ] symposium chairman or the [ 15 ] symposium organizer . All invited sessions should start with a tutorial paper .
